Purchase options and add-ons

How To Be Alive is a collection of Tara Booth's most recent gouache paintings. Straying from the narrative form of her first two publications, How To Be Alive is a series of densely patterned, colorful, one and two page vignettes that still build a story of Tara's life.

Editorial Reviews

About the Author

Tara Booth is an artist from Philadelphia, PA currently based in Portland, Oregon. Since she began making comics in 2015, her work has been published by küs! comics, Colorama Press, Brainfreeze Comics and in various anthologies.

About the author

Follow authors to get new release updates, plus improved recommendations.

Tara Booth

Brief content visible, double tap to read full content.
Full content visible, double tap to read brief content.

Tara Booth is an Ignatz Award winning comics artist, textile designer and illustrator from Philadelphia, known for her colorful, pattern-filled auto-biographical comics. Her work has been featured in Vice, Best American Comics, Juxtapoz Magazine, and It's Nice That- among other publications.

How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.
